The Road Traffic Management Corporation says that it will continue its operations into the coming long weekend. CAPE TOWN - Traffic officials have effected over 3,000 arrests across the country since 1 December. The Road Traffic Management Corporation's Simon Zwane says that the arrests have saved lives, including those of the arrested. We are continuing with this operation also for this coming long weekend. We think we have saved many lives and saved others from themselves. In terms of fatal accidents it's been quiet on Western Cape roads with no deaths reported since Sunday.(Edited by Neo Koza)